de.rwth.i2.attestor.graph.morphism

Interface FeasibilityFunction

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCompatibleNeighbours, CompatibleEdgeLabels, CompatibleExternalNodes, CompatibleNodeTypes, CompatiblePredecessors, CompatibleSuccessors, EmbeddingEdgeLabels, EmbeddingExternalNodes, IdenticalNodeTypes, MinAbstractionDistance, OneStepLookaheadIn, OneStepLookaheadOut, TwoStepLookahead, WeaklyCompatibleExternalNodes

    public interface FeasibilityFunction
    A FeasibilityFunction is a condition that is evaluated by a VF2Algorithm in order to determine whether extending a VF2State by a pair of candidate nodes might still correspond to a valid graph morphism.
    Author:
    Christoph

    • Method Detail

      • eval

        boolean eval(VF2State state,
             int p,
             int t)
        Evaluates whether extending the given state by a candidate pair results in a partial mapping between pattern and target Graph might still lead to a valid Morphism.
        Parameters:
        state - The current VF2State determining the partial Morphism computed so far.
        p - The new pattern candidate node that should be added to the morphism.
        t - The new target candidate node that should be added to the morphism.
        Returns:
        True if and only if adding the candidate pair to the current state of the morphism might still lead to a valid Morphism.
